dcterms:description: A professional hydrology data simulation system commonly used to generate synthetic datasets or calibrate realistic data samples based on physical modules. The dataset used in this paper is based on the synthetic data generated by the SWAT system, simulating the Root River Headwater watershed in Southeast Minnesota.
dcterms:title: SWAT (Soil & Water Assessment Tool)

dcterms:description: A dataset containing electronic healthcare records used to analyze causal effects in healthcare settings. The dataset is referenced in the context of teaching deep learning causal effects to improve predictive performance.
dcterms:title: EHR (Electronic Healthcare Records)
